If you've been to the Dominican Republic with a Dominican odds are you've had a chimi and most everything else on the menu of this relatively small and clean fast food joint. If you've never been to the DR or if you've never left the resort while you're there then you probably wouldn't be reading this review; be adventurous though and order up a chimi. It's basically a Dominican style burger (if you order the beef) or a chicken sandwich (if you get the chicken). I'd take this burger over anything made by McDonald's. It's packed with flavor not found on those frozen Mcpatties. Make sure you also try their super sized empanadas (a bit greasy but why else would you be here?). The menu is huge and everything looks delicious. This is the perfect late night stop after hitting the bar or lounge. Be warned, the place gets packed at night and on the weekends.
